President Cyril Ramaphosa is expected to address the nation at 8pm on Wednesday. Ramaphosa is expected to provide an update on the government's strategies to manage the coronavirus pandemic. PRETORIA - President Cyril Ramaphosa will address the nation on Wednesday at 8pm. Ramaphosa is expected to speak on measures government will take to curb the spread of the coronavirus. As of Tuesday night, there almost 20,000 reported COVID-19 related deaths in South Africa. READ: Ramaphosa wishes matrics well ahead of 2020 exams The cumulative number of detected infections is now at 740,254. In September, South Africa moved to Level 1 of the lockdown. The country has gradually and cautiously eased restrictions on international travel and social activities.  